es====\n''Avengers vs. X-Men'' dominated the sales charts in its first months of release, and was only beaten to the #1 spot by ''[[The Walking Dead (comics)|The Walking Dead]]'' #100 in July 2012, and ''[[Uncanny Avengers]]'' #1 in October 2012.<ref name=\"JulySales\">{{cite web |first=John |last=Mayo |date=2012-08-07 |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=40311 |title=Sales Estimates for July, 2012 - \"The Walking Dead\" Tops the Chart |website=Comic Book Resources |accessdate=2012-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120808234358/http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=40311 |archive-date=2012-08-08 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"OctoberSales\">{{cite web |first=John |last=Mayo |date=2012-11-13 |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=42165 |title=Sales Estimates for October, 2012 - \"Uncanny Avengers\" Debuts Big, \"Walking Dead\" Leaps Into Top 10 |website=Comic Book Resources |accessdate=2012-11-13 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6DdrC0UWq?url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article |archive-date=2013-01-13 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:auto; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=10%| Issue\n!width=30%| First month of publication\n!width=30%| Estimated no. of units sold\n!width=20%| Sales chart position\n!width=10%| Ref.\n|-\n|| #0\n|rowspan=\"2\"| March 2012\n|| 134,522\n|| 2\n|rowspan=\"2\"| <ref name=\"MarchSales\" />\n|-\n|| #1\n|| 203,200\n|| 1\n|-\n|| #2\n|| April 2012\n|| 158,650\n|| 1\n|| <ref name=\"AprilSales\">{{cite web |first=John |last=Mayo |date=2012-05-08 |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=38550 |title=Sales Estimates for April, 2012 - AvX Nabs Top Spot |website=Comic Book Resources |accessdate=2012-06-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120610182633/http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=38550 |archive-date=2012-06-10 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n|| #3\n|rowspan=\"2\"| May 2012\n|| 175,683\n|